        void onCredentialCreated(Credential credential,
                       TokenResponse tokenResponse)
                         throws java.io.IOException
        Notifies of a created credential after a successful token response in AuthorizationCodeFlow.createAndStoreCredential(com.google.api.client.auth.oauth2.TokenResponse, java.lang.String).

        Typical use is to parse additional fields from the credential created, such as an ID token.

        Parameters:
        credential - created credential
        tokenResponse - successful token response
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
